('cybersecurity','You run hashcat against an MD5 hash and it cracks in 2 seconds. Why is MD5 broken for password storage?','MD5 is too fast to compute, making brute force trivial','MD5 hashes are reversible','MD5 produces short hashes','MD5 requires a salt','A'),
('cybersecurity','You discover a SSRF vulnerability. What internal resource do you try to access first to confirm impact?','The AWS metadata endpoint at 169.254.169.254','The /etc/passwd file','The database server','The admin panel','B'),
('cybersecurity','During a pentest you find a page that makes server-side HTTP requests based on user input. What vulnerability is this?','XSS','CSRF','SSRF','XXE','C'),
('cybersecurity','You are told to test only app.example.com. You find a vulnerability on the main site. What do you do?','Exploit it since you are already on the engagement','Ignore it completely','Expand your scope without asking','Document and report it but do not exploit it as it is outside scope','D'),
('cybersecurity','You use sqlmap and confirm MySQL injection. You want to dump the users table from the webapp database. What flag?','sqlmap -u URL -D webapp -T users --dump','sqlmap -u URL --dump','sqlmap -u URL --extract users','sqlmap -u URL --table users --get','A'),
('cybersecurity','You are testing an API. You change /api/users/123 to /api/users/124 and get another users data. What is this?','SQL Injection','IDOR (Insecure Direct Object Reference)','CSRF','Privilege escalation','B'),
('cybersecurity','You find a JWT token with header alg set to none. What attack do you try?','Crack the JWT secret with hashcat','Replay the token from another session','Remove the signature to bypass authentication','Brute force the user ID in the payload','C'),
('cybersecurity','You find an XML input field. You inject an entity that reads /etc/passwd. What attack is this?','SQL Injection','XSS','Path Traversal','XXE (XML External Entity) Injection','D'),
('cybersecurity','You capture traffic with Wireshark and see credentials in plain text. What protocol is being used?','HTTP or Telnet or FTP which are unencrypted protocols','HTTPS','TLS 1.3','SSH','A'),
('cybersecurity','You use Metasploit and run "use exploit/multi/handler". What is this module used for?','Scanning for vulnerabilities','Listening for incoming reverse shell connections','Running SQL injection attacks','Cracking passwords','B'),
('cybersecurity','You run nikto against a web server and it reports "Server leaks inodes via ETags". Why is this a problem?','ETags slow down the server','It disables caching','It leaks inode numbers which can help attackers map the filesystem','It exposes the server SSL certificate','C'),
('cybersecurity','You run gobuster and find /backup. Inside is a database.sql file. What is this vulnerability called?','SQL Injection','Sensitive Data Exposure','SSRF','Sensitive file exposure via directory enumeration','D'),
('cybersecurity','You find a page with a file upload that accepts any file type. You upload a PHP webshell and it executes. What is this?','Unrestricted File Upload leading to Remote Code Execution','CSRF','LFI','XSS','A'),
('cybersecurity','You find a web app that uses JWT. You decode the payload and see role: user. What do you try?','Log out and log back in','Change role to admin and re-encode — test if the signature is verified','Generate a new token from the username','Replay the same token twice','B'),
('cybersecurity','You find a CSRF vulnerability on a bank transfer form. What makes CSRF attacks possible?','The server does not verify that requests originate from the legitimate site','The form uses POST instead of GET','The form has no input validation','The session cookie is HttpOnly','C'),
('cybersecurity','You run "sudo -l" on a compromised Linux machine and see the user can run /usr/bin/python3 as root. How do you exploit this?','Run python3 scripts as normal','Use python3 to scan the network','It cannot be exploited','Run sudo python3 with os.system to spawn a root shell','D'),
('cybersecurity','You are doing a pentest and find an admin panel at /admin with no authentication. What type of vulnerability is this?','Broken Access Control','SQL Injection','SSRF','Insecure Deserialization','A'),
('cybersecurity','You use Burp Suite Intruder to brute force a login form. After 20 requests you get 429 errors. What is this?','An injection vulnerability','Rate limiting protecting against brute force','An XSS filter','Session expiry','B'),
('cybersecurity','You are looking at an HTTP response and see the header X-Frame-Options: DENY. What attack does this prevent?','XSS','CSRF','Clickjacking','SQL Injection','C'),
('cybersecurity','You perform a pentest on an app running unpatched Apache Struts. What is your first step?','Immediately exploit it','Report it without verifying','Scan for other vulnerabilities','Look up known CVEs for that version on NVD or ExploitDB','D'),
('cybersecurity','You find a login page that takes 5 seconds to respond when a username exists but 0.1s when it does not. What does this enable?','Username enumeration via timing side channel','SQL Injection','CSRF','Credential stuffing','A'),
('cybersecurity','You crack a hash and get Summer2024!. This password fails against which protection?','Length requirements','Common password blacklisting','Complexity requirements','MFA','B'),
('cybersecurity','You are testing an app. The password reset link contains the user email as a query parameter. What do you test?','Whether the link expires','Whether the link uses HTTPS','Whether you can reset another users password by changing the email parameter','Whether the email is validated','C'),
('cybersecurity','You are pentesting a REST API and it returns stack traces in error responses. What is the risk?','It makes the API slower','It causes CSRF vulnerabilities','It leaks the database schema','Stack traces expose internal paths and library versions that help attackers','D'),
('cybersecurity','During recon you run subfinder against a domain. What are you looking for?','Subdomains that may have separate attack surfaces','Open ports on the main domain','SSL certificates','Email addresses','A'),
('cybersecurity','You gain a reverse shell but it is not fully interactive. You want to upgrade to a proper TTY. What do you use?','Use python3 to import the pty module and spawn /bin/bash','shell --upgrade','bash --login','sudo bash','B'),
('cybersecurity','You find an open redirect: /redirect?url=https://evil.com. Why is this dangerous?','It can be used in phishing — victims trust the legitimate domain in the URL','It breaks SEO','It bypasses CSRF protection','It causes XSS','C'),
('cybersecurity','You want to test if a company employees will click phishing links. What type of engagement is this?','Vulnerability assessment','Red team exercise','Physical pentest','Social engineering / phishing simulation','D'),
('cybersecurity','You run "strings" on a binary and find "password123". Where might this be used?','As a hardcoded credential or encryption key in the binary','Nowhere — strings in binaries are random','As a buffer overflow payload','As metadata only','A'),
('cybersecurity','You see a cookie with the flag HttpOnly=true. What does this prevent?','JavaScript from accessing the cookie, preventing XSS-based session theft','The cookie being sent over HTTP','The cookie being modified','The cookie from being deleted','B'),
('cybersecurity','You find a reflected XSS but the app filters the word script. What do you try?','Use an img tag with onerror handler as an alternative XSS payload','Add more script tags','Give up and report it as unexploitable','Try SQL injection instead','C'),
('cybersecurity','You discover a deserialization endpoint. The app deserializes user-supplied data without validation. What is the risk?','Data corruption only','XSS','CSRF','Remote Code Execution if a gadget chain exists','D'),
('cybersecurity','You find a web app vulnerable to LFI via /page?file=../../../etc/passwd. What do you try to escalate to RCE?','Try to include a log file containing code you injected earlier (log poisoning)','Read more system files','Use it to bypass authentication','Look for robots.txt via LFI','A'),
('cybersecurity','You are doing OSINT and want email addresses and subdomains for a company in one tool. Which do you use?','theHarvester','nmap','Wireshark','Burp Suite','B'),
('cybersecurity','You run "netstat -tlnp" on a server and see a service on 0.0.0.0:4444. What is suspicious?','Port 4444 is suspicious','Any port above 1024 is suspicious','The service is on localhost','0.0.0.0 means IPv6 only','C'),
('cybersecurity','You are pentesting an Android app and SSL pinning blocks your proxy. What do you try?','Switch to HTTP','Use a different proxy tool','Decompile the app and remove all HTTPS calls','Use Frida or objection to bypass SSL pinning at runtime','D'),
('cybersecurity','You find the admin password hash starting with $2b$12$. What algorithm is this?','bcrypt','MD5','SHA-256','SHA-1','A'),
('cybersecurity','You are reading a pentest report and see "P1 - Critical". What does this mean?','It requires immediate remediation and poses the highest risk','The finding is informational only','It is out of scope','It is a false positive','B'),
('cybersecurity','You run "ls -la /home" and see a folder "backups" owned by root with permissions 777. What is the implication?','The folder is read-only','The folder is encrypted','Any user can write to it — a potential privilege escalation vector','This is normal Linux behavior','C'),
('cybersecurity','You are pentesting a black box target with no prior information. What is your first step?','Perform passive and active recon to understand the attack surface','Launch Metasploit immediately','Try default credentials on everything','Run sqlmap on every form','D'),
('cybersecurity','Your scan finds port 3306 open on an external-facing server. What is the first concern?','MySQL is directly exposed to the internet and could be attacked remotely','Port 3306 is safe to expose','The port is only used for monitoring','Port 3306 is encrypted by default','A'),
('cybersecurity','You want to test if a company enforces HTTPS. You visit the HTTP version and check what happens. What are you testing for?','HTTP to HTTPS redirect and HSTS header enforcement','SQL Injection','Certificate pinning','Server version disclosure','B'),

-- ============================================================
-- DevOps & CI/CD (50)
-- ============================================================
('devops','Your production deployment is broken. You need to immediately revert to the last working version. What command?','kubectl rollout undo deployment/myapp','kubectl restart deployment myapp','kubectl delete deployment myapp then apply old yaml','kubectl set image deployment/myapp myapp=old-image','A'),
('devops','Your Docker container builds fine but crashes immediately when you run it. What is the first command you run?','docker inspect mycontainer','docker logs mycontainer','docker stats mycontainer','docker exec -it mycontainer sh','B'),
('devops','Your GitHub Actions workflow downloads npm packages every run, taking 8 minutes. What do you add to fix this?','Run npm install --production only','Use a smaller runner','Use the actions/cache action to cache node_modules between runs','Run npm ci instead of npm install','C'),
('devops','You push to main and CI fails with "permission denied" when pushing a Docker image to the registry. What is missing?','The Dockerfile is wrong','The image name is wrong','Docker is not installed on the runner','The CI pipeline is missing registry credentials stored as secrets','D'),
('devops','Your Kubernetes pod is stuck in CrashLoopBackOff. What sequence of commands do you run to diagnose?','kubectl describe pod name then kubectl logs name --previous','kubectl get pods then kubectl delete pod','kubectl restart pod name','kubectl get events only','A'),
('devops','You deploy to Kubernetes and users report downtime during the deployment. What strategy prevents this?','Recreate strategy','Both rolling update with readiness probes and blue/green deployments prevent downtime','Rolling update only','Blue/green deployment only','B'),
('devops','Your docker-compose app works locally but containers cannot talk to each other in production. Most common reason?','The containers have different base images','The ports are wrong in the Dockerfile','The containers are not on the same Docker network','Docker Compose is not installed in production','C'),
('devops','Your Kubernetes deployment has 3 replicas but 2 pods are stuck in Pending. What do you check?','Pod restart count','The container image','The service selector','Node resources — the cluster may not have enough CPU or memory to schedule the pods','D'),
('devops','You want GitHub Actions to run only when files in src/ change, not when README.md changes. What do you add?','A paths filter under the push trigger','An if: condition on each step','A separate workflow file for docs','A manual approval step','A'),
('devops','Your Jenkins pipeline fails because a shell script exits with code 1 but output looks fine. What do you check?','The Jenkins version','The script likely has a command that exits with 1 even on success — check the specific failing command','Increase Jenkins heap size','Run the pipeline on a different agent','B'),
('devops','You need to pass a database password to a Kubernetes pod securely. What resource do you create?','A ConfigMap','An environment variable in the Deployment YAML','A Kubernetes Secret','A mounted volume with the password in a file','C'),
('devops','Your Helm chart deployment fails with "release already exists". What do you run?','helm install again with --force','helm delete then helm install','helm rollback','helm upgrade --install which handles both install and upgrade','D'),
('devops','You want a Kubernetes pod to only start receiving traffic after it passes a health check. What do you configure?','A readinessProbe','A livenessProbe','A startupProbe','An initContainer','A'),
('devops','Your Docker image is 4GB and builds and pulls are slow. What is the most effective fix?','Compress files inside the container','Use a smaller base image like alpine and use multi-stage builds','Remove the .git folder','Use docker squash','B'),
('devops','You run kubectl top nodes and see a node at 95% memory. New pods are immediately OOMKilled. What do you do?','Restart the node','Increase pod memory requests','Drain the node and scale up the cluster or set resource limits on pods','Delete the pods being killed','C'),
('devops','Your CI/CD deploys to production on every merge. A bad commit slips through. What process was missing?','More unit tests','A bigger test suite','Feature flags','A staging environment and manual approval gate before production','D'),
('devops','You want to run a database migration before your new app version starts in Kubernetes. Best approach?','Use a Kubernetes Job or initContainer that runs the migration before the main container starts','Add the migration to the app startup code','Run it manually before deploying','Add it as a separate Deployment','A'),
('devops','Your Dockerfile has 15 layers and npm install runs every time even when package.json has not changed. Fix?','Use --no-cache flag','COPY package.json first, run npm install, then COPY the rest of the source code','Combine all RUN commands','Use a smaller base image','B'),
('devops','You need to debug an issue inside a running Kubernetes pod. What command runs a shell inside it?','kubectl ssh pod/name','kubectl debug pod/name','kubectl exec -it pod-name -- /bin/sh','kubectl attach pod-name','C'),
('devops','Your GitHub Actions job takes 45 minutes of linting, testing, and building. How do you speed it up?','Use a faster runner','Remove some tests','Cache the entire workspace','Split into parallel jobs — lint, test, and build running at the same time','D'),
('devops','You have a Kubernetes ClusterIP service but need to access it from your local machine for debugging. What do you use?','kubectl port-forward service/myservice 8080:80','Change it to NodePort','Create an Ingress','Use kubectl proxy','A'),
('devops','A pod keeps getting OOMKilled. Memory limit is 256Mi but the app needs 400Mi. What do you do?','Optimize the application code','Increase the memory limit in the pod spec to at least 400Mi','Remove the memory limit entirely','Restart the pod more frequently','B'),
('devops','You want to deploy to Kubernetes with different config per environment. Cleanest solution?','Hardcode values in the image','Build separate Docker images per environment','Use Helm values files — values.dev.yaml and values.prod.yaml','Use environment variables in the Dockerfile','C'),
('devops','Your team wants all Docker images in Kubernetes to come from your private registry only. Where do you enforce this?','In each developer local Docker config','In the Dockerfile FROM line','In the CI pipeline only','With an OPA/Gatekeeper admission controller policy in Kubernetes','D'),
('devops','You deployed the same image to staging and it works. You want to promote the exact same image to production. What do you do?','Pull the same image tag that was deployed to staging and deploy it to production','Rebuild the image from the same commit','Run the CI pipeline again on main','Deploy from the feature branch directly','A'),
('devops','Your Kubernetes HPA is not scaling up even though CPU is at 90%. What is a common reason?','HPA only scales down','Both metrics server missing and no resource requests defined can cause this','The deployment has no resource requests defined','The metrics server is not installed in the cluster','B'),
('devops','You want a specific pod to run on every node in your cluster. What Kubernetes resource do you use?','Deployment with replicas equal to node count','StatefulSet','DaemonSet','ReplicaSet','C'),
('devops','Your CI pipeline tags Docker images as latest every time. A teammate pulls latest and gets an outdated image. Fix?','Clear Docker cache more often','Use docker pull --force','Rebuild images more frequently','Tag images with the git commit SHA or build number instead of just latest','D'),
('devops','You want Kubernetes to automatically restart pods that fail their health check. What probe handles this?','livenessProbe','readinessProbe','startupProbe','healthProbe','A'),
('devops','You run terraform plan and see 2 unexpected destroys. You expected zero changes. What do you do?','Run terraform apply immediately','Investigate why those resources are being destroyed before applying','Ignore the destroys as they are old','Run terraform refresh to fix the state','B'),
('devops','Your team frequently pushes broken code to main. What workflow change prevents this?','More commit messages','Commit directly to main with more care','Require pull requests with code review approval and passing CI before merging','Use git stash more often','C'),
('devops','You want to see CPU and memory usage of all pods across the cluster right now. What command?','kubectl get pods --resources','kubectl describe nodes','kubectl get metrics','kubectl top pods --all-namespaces','D'),
('devops','Your Ansible playbook runs fine the first time but fails on the second run because the resource exists. Fix?','Make the tasks idempotent using Ansible modules that handle already-exists gracefully','Delete the resource before running','Run with --skip-existing flag','Add a check task before every create task','A'),
('devops','Your GitHub Actions workflow needs to deploy to AWS. What is the modern approach instead of static credentials?','Use OIDC to let GitHub Actions assume an IAM role without static credentials','Store them as base64 encoded secrets','Rotate credentials every month','Store them in a .env file in the repo','B'),
('devops','A pod in your cluster needs to call the Kubernetes API. What provides its identity for RBAC?','The pod IP address','The namespace it runs in','A ServiceAccount bound to an RBAC Role','The node it runs on','C'),
('devops','You want to roll back a Helm release to the previous revision. What command do you run?','helm revert myapp','helm undo myapp','helm install myapp --previous','helm rollback myapp 1','D'),
('devops','Your Docker build fails with "COPY failed: file not found in build context". What is wrong?','The file path in COPY is wrong or the file does not exist in the directory where you ran docker build','The file is corrupted','The base image is missing the file','Docker cannot access the filesystem','A'),
('devops','You want staging to be an exact replica of production at lower scale. Best practice?','Manually set up staging to be similar','Use the same Terraform code with different variable values for instance counts and sizes','Use production snapshot','Share the same database as production','B'),
('devops','A critical security patch needs to be deployed today but CI takes 2 hours. What do you do?','Skip CI entirely and push directly','Wait for the full 2-hour pipeline','Deploy manually from your laptop','Run only the security-critical tests in a fast-path pipeline and get approval to deploy','C'),
('devops','You want a Kubernetes pod in EKS to access S3 without static credentials. What do you use?','An IAM user with S3 access','Environment variables with access keys','A Kubernetes Secret containing AWS credentials','IRSA (IAM Roles for Service Accounts)','D'),
('devops','Your pipeline fails because two parallel jobs try to update the same Terraform state file. What do you add?','State locking via DynamoDB backend and serialize plan/apply jobs','A retry mechanism','Separate state files per job','Increase pipeline timeout','A'),
('devops','You run kubectl get svc and see your service has ClusterIP: None. What type of service is this?','A headless service used for stateful applications or direct pod DNS','An external service','A misconfigured service','A LoadBalancer without an IP yet','B'),
('devops','You want to automatically build and push a Docker image every time code merges to main. What trigger do you use?','on: schedule','on: pull_request','on: push: branches: [main]','on: workflow_dispatch','C'),
('devops','Your Kubernetes cluster is on version 1.25 and you want to upgrade to 1.28. What is the correct approach?','Upgrade directly from 1.25 to 1.28','Recreate the cluster from scratch','Upgrade all nodes simultaneously','Upgrade one minor version at a time: 1.25 to 1.26 to 1.27 to 1.28','D'),
('devops','You want every Docker image in your CI pipeline checked for critical CVEs before deployment. What do you add?','A container image scanning step using Trivy or Snyk','A manual security review step','A size check on the image','A Dockerfile linter','A'),
('devops','Your Kubernetes namespace keeps hitting its resource quota and new pods cannot be created. What do you check?','Total CPU and memory requested by existing pods versus the namespace quota','Number of services in the namespace','Number of ConfigMaps','Network policies','B'),
('devops','You want to expose a Kubernetes service externally on a domain with HTTPS. What combination do you need?','NodePort with SSL on the app','LoadBalancer service only','Ingress controller plus TLS secret plus Ingress resource plus cert-manager','ClusterIP with external DNS','C'),
('devops','A teammate ran terraform destroy and deleted the production database. What should have prevented this?','Better documentation','A backup only','Manual Terraform runs only','lifecycle prevent_destroy = true on the database resource and restricted CI permissions','D'),
('devops','You want to run a one-time data migration job in Kubernetes that completes and exits. What resource do you create?','A Kubernetes Job','A Deployment with replicas: 1','A CronJob','A DaemonSet','A'),
('devops','You notice pods are only scheduled on 3 out of 10 Ready nodes. What do you check?','Node OS versions','Whether the pods have node selectors, affinity rules, or taints limiting scheduling','Network plugin configuration','Kubernetes version on each node','B'),

-- ============================================================
-- Data Science, Analytics & Big Data (50)
-- ============================================================
('data_science','Your model gets 99% accuracy on training data but 55% on test data. What is happening and what do you do first?','The model is overfitting — try regularization, reduce complexity, or add more training data','The model is underfitting — add more features','The test data is wrong — reshuffle and retry','The accuracy metric is incorrect — switch to F1','A'),
('data_science','You load a CSV and a column has 40% NaN values. What do you do before deciding how to handle it?','Drop it immediately','Check if the missingness is random or related to other features before deciding to impute or drop','Fill all NaN with 0','Fill all NaN with the mean','B'),
('data_science','You have a dataset with 95% class 0 and 5% class 1. Your model predicts 0 for everything and gets 95% accuracy. What metric do you actually need?','Accuracy is fine for this task','Use MSE instead','Precision, recall, F1-score or AUC-ROC which account for class imbalance','Accuracy with a threshold of 0.5','C'),
('data_science','You run df.info() and see a column "price" has dtype object even though it should be numeric. What is the actual fix?','Cast it with df["price"].astype(float)','Fill NaN values first','Drop the column','The column has non-numeric characters like dollar sign or comma — clean it first then convert','D'),
('data_science','You trained a model on Jan-Nov data and tested on December. It works great but fails in production. Why?','The model has too many features','December is always an outlier month','The model needs retraining monthly','Data leakage — the model was trained on data including future info not available at prediction time','A'),
('data_science','You need to join two DataFrames on user_id and keep all rows from the left even with no right match. What do you use?','pd.merge(df1, df2, on="user_id", how="inner")','pd.merge(df1, df2, on="user_id", how="left")','pd.concat([df1, df2])','df1.join(df2, on="user_id")','B'),
('data_science','Your scikit-learn model gives different results on your machine versus your colleagues machine with same data. What did you forget?','To save the model','To normalize the data','To set random_state to a fixed value in the model and train_test_split','To print the results','C'),
('data_science','You want to find which features matter most in your Random Forest model. What do you access?','model.weights_','model.coef_','model.explain()','model.feature_importances_','D'),
('data_science','You run a SQL query and get duplicate rows in the result. What clause do you add to remove them?','DISTINCT','GROUP BY','UNIQUE','DEDUPE','A'),
('data_science','You need the top 3 salaries per department in SQL. Simple ORDER BY and LIMIT does not work across departments. What do you use?','A subquery with MAX()','ROW_NUMBER() or DENSE_RANK() partitioned by department','GROUP BY department ORDER BY salary','A self-join','B'),
('data_science','Your pandas groupby on a 10 million row DataFrame is very slow. What do you consider switching to?','A faster computer','NumPy groupby','PySpark or Dask for distributed computation','SQL in pandas','C'),
('data_science','You want to evaluate your model fairly but only have 1000 samples. Train/test split wastes data. What technique?','Use all data for training and none for testing','Increase your dataset artificially','Use leave-one-out only','k-fold cross-validation','D'),
('data_science','You computed the correlation matrix and two features have correlation of 0.98. What do you do?','Consider removing one to reduce multicollinearity, especially for linear models','Keep both because more features is always better','Replace both with their average','Normalize both features','A'),
('data_science','You run df.describe() and notice the max of a column is 999999 while the 75th percentile is 50. What does this suggest?','The data is normally distributed','There are significant outliers that may skew your model','The column needs to be log-transformed','The data is correct','B'),
('data_science','You plot "age" (0-100) and "income" (0-1000000). Your KNN model performs poorly. Why and what do you do?','KNN does not support large numbers — use log transform','The model needs more neighbors k','The features are irrelevant','KNN is distance-based so income dominates — apply StandardScaler or MinMaxScaler first','C'),
('data_science','You are building a recommendation system and users say recommendations are too similar to what they already bought. What problem is this?','Overfitting','Data leakage','Model underfitting','The filter bubble — too much exploitation and not enough exploration','D'),
('data_science','Your model training takes 6 hours and you want to experiment with hyperparameters. What do you use instead of manual tuning?','GridSearchCV or RandomizedSearchCV or Optuna for automated hyperparameter tuning','Try all combinations manually','Only tune one parameter at a time','Train for fewer epochs','A'),
('data_science','You have a time series dataset and accidentally shuffle data before splitting into train and test. What went wrong?','Shuffling is always fine','Future data leaked into training — time series splits must respect temporal order','The split ratio is wrong','You need more data','B'),
('data_science','You want to apply a custom function to every row of a pandas DataFrame using multiple columns. What is the most readable approach?','Use a for loop','Use df.map(func)','Use df.apply(func, axis=1)','Use numpy vectorize','C'),
('data_science','You build a logistic regression for churn prediction. The business asks "of all churned customers, how many did we catch?" Which metric is this?','Precision','F1-score','Accuracy','Recall','D'),
('data_science','Your Spark job fails with OutOfMemoryError on the driver. What is the most likely cause?','You called .collect() on a large RDD or DataFrame, pulling all data to the driver','Too many workers','The cluster is too small','The data format is wrong','A'),
('data_science','You call df.merge() and end up with far more rows than either original DataFrame. What happened?','The merge created duplicates','You used the wrong merge type','The join key has duplicate values in both DataFrames causing a many-to-many join explosion','One DataFrame is repeated','B'),
('data_science','You want to find customers who purchased in 2024 but NOT in 2023. What SQL approach works?','WHERE year = 2024 AND year != 2023','GROUP BY year HAVING year = 2024','Customers from 2024 EXCEPT customers from 2023, or a LEFT JOIN with IS NULL filter','INNER JOIN between 2024 and 2023 tables','C'),
('data_science','You train a model and pickle it. Six months later predictions are wrong with no code changes. What happened?','The pickle file is corrupted','The Python version changed','The model was not trained properly','Model drift — the real-world data distribution changed since training','D'),
('data_science','You want to reduce a 500-feature dataset to 50 features. Which technique preserves the most variance?','PCA — keeping the top 50 principal components that explain the most variance','Randomly drop 450 features','Drop features with the lowest mean','Use only features with no missing values','A'),
('data_science','Your SQL query on a 50 million row table is very slow. You are filtering by user_id. What do you check first?','Whether the query is written correctly','Whether there is an index on the user_id column','The database server memory','Whether the table is partitioned','B'),
('data_science','You want to detect anomalies in server metrics with no labeled training data. What approach fits?','Train a supervised classifier with normal/anomaly labels','Use linear regression','Use unsupervised methods like Isolation Forest or Autoencoder','Use K-Means with K=2','C'),
('data_science','You use LabelEncoder on your target variable before train/test split. Your colleague says this can bug. Why?','LabelEncoder does not work with strings','LabelEncoder changes the distribution','LabelEncoder should be applied after splitting','If new categories appear in test that were not in training, LabelEncoder will throw an error','D'),
('data_science','You want to standardize your preprocessing and model into a single object that can be fit and applied consistently. What do you use?','A Pipeline','A dictionary of steps','A ColumnTransformer only','A FunctionTransformer','A'),
('data_science','Your A/B test shows variant B has 2% higher conversion. The p-value is 0.08. Can you conclude B is better?','Yes, 2% improvement is meaningful','No, p-value > 0.05 means the result is not statistically significant at the standard threshold','Yes because the sample size is large','No, you need to run the test longer regardless of p-value','B'),
('data_science','You apply pd.get_dummies() to a column with 5 categories and get 5 new columns. What problem can this cause with linear models?','Too many columns slow down training','The model will ignore the new columns','Nothing, this is always correct','Multicollinearity — dummy variable trap. You should drop one category with drop_first=True','C'),
('data_science','You notice your model always predicts the majority class in an imbalanced dataset. What do you try first?','Get more data','Switch to a different model type','Increase the number of trees','Use class_weight="balanced" or SMOTE to handle the imbalance','D'),
('data_science','You have sales data by day and want to compute a 7-day rolling average. What pandas method do you use?','df["sales"].rolling(7).mean()','df["sales"].resample("7D").mean()','df["sales"].cumsum() / 7','df["sales"].ewm(span=7).mean()','A'),
('data_science','You are presenting model results to non-technical stakeholders. Your RMSE is 450. They ask "is that good?". What do you say?','Yes, our model is accurate','RMSE of 450 means our predictions are off by 450 units on average — let me compare this to a baseline','RMSE is a complex metric requiring technical understanding','It depends on the model architecture','B'),
('data_science','You run EXPLAIN on a slow SQL query and see "Seq Scan" on a large table. What does this mean and what should you add?','The query is optimized already','Sequential scan is faster than index scan','The table is too large to index','The database is doing a full table scan — add an index on the filtered column','C'),
('data_science','You want to visualize the relationship between two continuous variables and show the distribution of each. What plot?','Two separate histograms','A heatmap','A bar chart','A seaborn jointplot or scatter plot with marginal distributions','D'),
('data_science','Your feature engineering created 200 new features from 20 originals. Model performance dropped. What likely happened?','The curse of dimensionality and noise from irrelevant features hurt the model','The model needs more training time','The features are not normalized','The model type is wrong','A'),
('data_science','You want to cache a heavy Spark computation you will reuse multiple times in the same session. What do you call?','df.cache() or df.persist()','df.save()','df.checkpoint()','df.collect()','B'),
('data_science','You want to count orders per customer and show only customers with more than 5 orders. What SQL do you write?','WHERE COUNT(orders) > 5','WHERE orders > 5 GROUP BY customer_id','GROUP BY customer_id HAVING COUNT(orders) > 5','HAVING orders > 5','C'),
('data_science','You computed feature importance and user_id is the most important feature. Why is this a red flag?','User IDs are always important','Random Forest always ranks IDs first','It means your model is accurate','User ID is an identifier — the model is memorizing individual users, not learning patterns','D'),
('data_science','Your pandas code works but is very slow because you use a for loop over 1 million rows. What is the idiomatic fix?','Vectorize the operation using pandas and numpy operations that work on entire columns at once','Use multiprocessing','Use df.apply() which is always faster','Use Cython','A'),
('data_science','You want to deploy your scikit-learn model as a REST API. What is a common lightweight approach?','Email the pickle file to the requester','Wrap it with Flask or FastAPI, load the pickled model, and expose a /predict endpoint','Use Jupyter notebooks as an API','Deploy directly from a Jupyter notebook','B'),
('data_science','You have a DataFrame with a datetime column and want all rows from the last 7 days. What is the pandas approach?','df[df["date"] > "last_7_days"]','df.tail(7)','df[df["date"] >= pd.Timestamp.now() - pd.Timedelta(days=7)]','df.filter(days=7)','C'),
('data_science','You trained a model and the precision is 0.90 but recall is 0.40. What does this mean in plain terms?','The model is accurate but slow','The model is overfitting','The threshold should be lowered to 0.3','When the model predicts positive it is usually right (90%) but it misses 60% of actual positives','D'),
('data_science','You want to find the second highest salary in a SQL table without using LIMIT or OFFSET. What query works?','SELECT MAX(salary) FROM employees WHERE salary < (SELECT MAX(salary) FROM employees)','SELECT MAX(salary) WHERE salary != MAX(salary)','SELECT salary ORDER BY salary DESC ROW 2','Use a subquery with RANK() = 2','A'),
('data_science','You want to update all rows where status is pending to active in pandas. What is the correct approach?','df.loc[df["status"] == "pending", "status"] = "active"','df["status"] = "active"','df.update({"status":"active"}, where="pending")','df.replace("pending").set("active")','B'),
('data_science','Your neural network loss is not decreasing after 10 epochs. What do you try first?','Add more layers','Add more training data','Check the learning rate — too high causes oscillation, too low causes no progress','Change the loss function','C'),
('data_science','You have a DataFrame with a datetime column and want to group by month. What is the pandas approach?','df.groupby(df["date"].dt.month).agg(...)','df.group("month").agg(...)','df.resample("M").first()','df.pivot_table(index="month")','D'),
('data_science','You are computing average order value per customer per month on 500 GB of data and pandas crashes. What do you use?','PySpark with groupBy and agg operations on a cluster','A larger pandas machine','Break data into chunks manually','NumPy instead of pandas','A'),
('data_science','You split your dataset into train, validation, and test sets. When do you use the test set?','Only once at the very end to report final model performance','After every training epoch to track progress','During hyperparameter tuning to pick the best model','Interchangeably with the validation set','B');
